{"type":"message","id":"202ccbb1","parentId":"ee64ae1d","timestamp":"2026-03-08T17:34:22.688Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying they're using Claude OAuth (not a direct API key). This means they're using the Claude.ai OAuth/subscription, not the Anthropic API with a pay-as-you-go key. The `sk-ant-oat01` token is an OAuth token - which aligns with what they're saying.\n\nWith Claude OAuth (Claude.ai subscription), there's no \"balance\" per se - it's a subscription model. Usage limits are based on the subscription plan (Pro, Team, etc.) rather than a credit balance.\n\nFor OAuth users:\n- There's no API billing dashboard\n- Usage is tied to their Claude.ai subscription\n- They can check their subscription/plan at claude.ai/settings\n\n\n- I should look into whether the Claude.ai API or any available tools expose usage data through the OAuth token, though this might not be available for subscription-based access.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"Got it — that changes things. With Claude OAuth (Claude.ai subscription), there's no credit balance to check — it's a subscription plan with usage limits, not pay-per-token billing."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_013wEFi55hcU4MmYgAKKEHUg","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ANTHROPIC_TOKEN=\"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\"\n\n# Try Claude.ai API with OAuth token to get account/subscription info\necho \"=== Claude.ai account ===\"\ncurl -s \"https://claude.ai/api/account\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $ANTHROPIC_TOKEN\" | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -30\n\necho \"\"\necho \"=== Claude.ai organizations ===\"\ncurl -s \"https://claude.ai/api/organizations\" \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer $ANTHROPIC_TOKEN\" | python3 -m json.tool 2>/dev/null | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output"