{"type":"message","id":"659b0b2a","parentId":"77935369","timestamp":"2026-03-08T17:37:04.151Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants to know their Claude usage percentage (how much of their rate limit they've used). With Claude OAuth, there are message limits (e.g., Pro gets ~45 messages per 5 hours for Opus, more for Sonnet). \n\nThe only way to get this info is through claude.ai's API which requires browser session cookies. Since there's no Chrome/browser available on the machine, I can't automate this. \n\nBut wait - let me check if there's any way OpenClaw tracks this, or if there's a Claude API endpoint I can hit with the OAuth token to get usage/rate limit info. Some APIs return rate limit headers in responses.\n\nLet me try making an API call and checking the response headers for rate limit info.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"toolu_01A6aec125CTWbb3CqssDgN7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ANTHROPIC_TOKEN=\"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\"\n\n# Make a minimal API call and capture ALL response headers - rate limit info is often in headers\ncurl -si \"https://api.anthropic.com/v1/messages\" \\\n  -H \"anthropic-version: 2023-06-01\" \\\n  -H \"x-api-key: $ANTHROPIC_TOKEN\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\"model\":\"claude-3-haiku-20240307\",\"max_tokens\":1,\"messages\":[{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":\"hi\"}]}' \\\n  2>/dev/null | grep -E \"^(HTTP|x-ratelimit|anthropic-ratelimit|retry|x-request|<)\" -i | head -30"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"anthropic","model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","usage":{"input":3,"output":500,"cacheRead":35023,"cacheWrite":130,"totalTokens":35656,"cost":{"input":0.000009,"output":0.007500000000000001,"cacheRead":0.0105069,"cacheWrite":0.00048750000000000003,"total":0.0185034}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772991410357}}
